# Mapping My Experience to Cloud + Security + FinOps

This document connects my past experience directly to the roles I’m building into.

---

## Military (20 Years)

### What I did:
- Led teams under pressure
- Managed classified systems and secure environments
- Oversaw personnel, operations, logistics, and readiness
- Enforced standards, compliance, and accountability
- Used defense-in-depth thinking daily

### Maps to Cloud/Security:
- Identity & Access Management mind-set
- Security controls & governance
- Risk assessment
- Incident response discipline
- “Assume breach” mentality before Zero Trust existed

---

## Supply Chain + Operations (Post-Navy Career)

### What I did:
- Managed $37M+ budgets
- Handled vendor contracts and cost negotiations
- Implemented process controls and audits
- Ensured compliance and operational continuity
- Led cross-functional teams

### Maps to FinOps + Governance:
- Cloud budget ownership
- Forecasting usage & spend
- Optimization mindset
- Documentation & workflows
- Policy development & operational standards

---

## MBA + Leadership
- Business strategy
- Finance fundamentals
- Accountability
- Data-driven decisions

### Maps to:
- FinOps KPIs
- Cloud spend analysis
- Cost-benefit evaluation
- Operational governance

---

## Summary

My background naturally aligns with:

- Cloud Security
- IAM
- Zero Trust
- FinOps / Cloud Cost Governance
